ary" href="assets/jamie_parr_public_cv.pdf" download>Download CV</a><a class="button button-ghost" href="mailto:jamieparr05@hotmail.com">Contact me</a></div><p class="kbd-hint">Tip: press <kbd>/</kbd> anywhere to jump around this site.</p></div><aside class="hero-aside" aria-label="Profile summary"><div class="portrait-card"><img class="portrait" src="assets/jamie-parr-headshot.jpg" alt="Headshot of Jamie Parr"><div class="portrait-copy"><h2>Jamie Parr</h2><p>Computing Technologies student at Ulster University</p></div></div><div class="proof-card"><div class="status-row"><span class="status-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>Preparing for a 2027/28 placement</span></div><div class="live-strip" id="live-strip" hidden><p class="live-strip-label">Live from my projects</p><ul><li id="live-coast-row" hidden><span class="live-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span><a href="https://coastinternetradio.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Coast Internet Radio</a><span id="live-coast-text"></span></li><li id="live-track-row" hidden><span id="live-track-text"></span></li><li id="live-commit-row" hidden><a id="live-commit-link" href="https://github.com/JamieP-205" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Latest push</a><span id="live-commit-text"></span></li></ul></div><dl class="quick-facts"><div><dt>Flagship builds</dt><dd>The World Forgot Us, French for Life and Groundwork</dd></div><div><dt>Production work</dt><dd>Coast Internet Radio, Talk With Jamie and Local Web Fix</dd></div><div><dt>Looking for</dt><dd>Software, web development and IT placements</dd></div></dl></div></aside></div></section><section id="about" class="section section-pad"><div class="container two-col"><div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">About</p><h2>Building practical experience before my placement year.</h2></div><div class="section-copy"><p>I have worked alongside study since 2021, mainly across warehouse, stockroom and service environments. That has given me a useful mix of practical experience: packing orders, sorting stock, supporting deliveries, helping customers, following procedures and staying calm during busy shifts.</p><p>My technical projects are where I apply that same practical mindset. I prefer to build something complete enough to test, document and explain honestly, including the limitations, rather than stop at a polished screen. I am preparing for a third-year placement in 2027/28 where I can keep learning from an experienced team.</p></div></div></section><section id="skills" class="section section-pad"><div class="container"><div class="section-heading narrow"><p class="eyebrow">Skills</p><h2>Skills demonstrated across working software, not only coursework.</h2><p>The projects below cover frontend and backend work, local data systems, game development, automated checks, deployment and the decisions needed to keep products reliable and understandable.</p></div><div class="skill-grid"><article class="skill-card"><h3>Development</h3><ul class="tag-list" aria-label="Development skills"><li>HTML</li><li>CSS</li><li>JavaScript</li><li>TypeScript</li><li>React</li><li>Next.js</li><li>Python fundamentals</li><li>SQL and SQLite</li><li>Godot 4</li><li>Git and GitHub</li><li>Netlify Functions</li><li>Cloudflare Workers</li></ul></article><article class="skill-card"><h3>Quality and systems</h3><ul class="tag-list" aria-label="Quality and systems skills"><li>Playwright</li><li>Vitest</li><li>Deterministic testing</li><li>GitHub Actions</li><li>Res